                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 233.) I took Horner at a coffee-8hop, in Peter's-lane, St. John-street—a person I went with went in, and asked for Mr. Hamer, and the landlord put his finger out to call, and Horner came out—the person with me said, This is the gentleman," and I asked him to walk with me, and took him to the station.</p>
